<p id="Par25">Both measures indicate the degree of spatial association of the dataset. The Moranʼs I index calculates the spatial autocorrelation as a covariance, from the product of the deviations from the mean [
 <xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR24">24</xref>]. This index indicates the magnitude of the spatial association present in the data set with n locations. The Moranʼs I index is calculated by the following expression:
 <disp-formula id="Equb">
